NAVAL COOPERATION AND GUIDANCE TO SHIPPING (NCAGS) ORGANIZATION WILL BE ESTABLISHED TO INTERACT WITH MERCHANT SHIPPING AND SUPPORT NAVAL OPERATIONS. NAVAL VESSELS AND AIRCRAFT REGULARLY EXERCISE PREVENTATIVE MEASURES IN ORDER TO SECURE THE CONTINUOUS AND INNOCENT PASSAGE OF MERCHANT SHIPPING DURING LIVE OPERATIONS INCLUDING COUNTER PIRACY. FOR THIS REASON, ALL MERCHANT VESSELS WITHIN OR ON PASSAGE THROUGH THESE AREAS ARE INVITED TO PARTICIPATE IN THE EXERCISE ON A NO-COST/NO-DELAY BASIS. 4. FOR VOLUNTARY PARTICIPATION BY MERCHANT VESSELS, EAST BOUND VESSELS ARE REQUESTED TO REPORT 12 HOURS BEFORE PASSING 003-00E. WEST BOUND VESSELS 12 HOURS BEFORE PASSING 011-00E AND VESSELS LEAVING PORTS WITHIN THE EXERCISE AREA SHOULD REPORT SIX HOURS BEFORE SAILING TO THE NATO SHIPPING CENTRE: E-MAIL: INFO@SHIPPING.NATO.INT, PHONE: 44 19 2395 6574, FAX: 44 192 3956 5754. 5. THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION WILL BE REQUIRED: A. VESSEL NAME. B. IMO NUMBER. C. INMARSAT AND E-MAIL CONTACT DETAILS. D. CURRENT POSITION. E. TRANSIT SPEED THROUGH AREA. F. INTENDED MOVEMENTS. 6. ALL MERCHANT VESSELS WITHIN OR APPROACHING THE EXERCISE AREA MAY BE CONTACTED BY PARTICIPATING NAVAL VESSELS. 7. CANCEL THIS MSG 08 OCT 12.
